title: Administrative | Polling Places
description: A polling place or polling location is where voters cast their ballots in elections.  The relationship between voting precincts and polling places is maintained in the PrecinctPollingPlace table and this table should be used to manage the unique occurrence of polling places to precincts; as well as occurrences that require many voting precincts to be related to a single polling place.

title: OpenDataStandards | Centerline
description:
Summary
Centerline data was developed for cartographic and geocoding purposes.  The attributes of the centerline data are in the MetroGIS Standard format.

Description
The geometry of the centerline data is created and maintained by the Carver County's Survey Department.  The attribution of the centerline data is a collaborative effort between the Survey Office and GIS Office.

title: OpenDataStandards | Address Points
description:
Summary Carver County address point dataset.
Description

Address points are maintained by different addressing authorities within Carver County. The dataset is based upon the MetroGIS Address Points Standards, derived from the National Address Standard. This dataset contains situs addresses, they are not used for contact of individuals, but instead for the relating of features to a specific location.

title: MnTopo Elevation Viewer
description:
MnTOPO is a web application for viewing, printing and downloading high-resolution elevation data for the State of Minnesota that was collected using LiDAR technology.

It runs on a variety of devices including desktop PCs, tablets, and mobile phones.

The data you see and download in MnTOPO was made possible by the Minnesota elevation mapping project.

MnTOPO is a collaborative effort between staff from the Minnesota Information Technology (MN.IT) @ Minnesota Department of Natural Resources and MN.IT @ Minnesota Geospatial Information Office (MnGeo). Funding was provided by the Clean Water Fund of the Clean Water, Land and Legacy Amendment.

title: OpenDataStandards l Parcels
description:
Summary
Parcel data was developed to map and track property boundaries. The attributes of the parcel data are in the MetroGIS Standard format.

Description

The geometry of parcels were created by Carver County's Survey department using COGO in an AutoCad environment. The AutoCad lines have been imported into a ArcGIS Geodatabase and polygons built. These polygons are attributed with a Parcel Identification Number (PID). The GIS polygons are joined by PID to the Assessor's CAMA system and Taxpayer Services tax database to show attributes of the property.
